description:
The reference mermaid.js automatically computes derived colors from base colors. Our implementation requires all colors to be specified manually.

**Reference pattern:**
```javascript
class Theme {
  constructor() {
    this.primaryColor = '#ECECFF';
  }

  updateColors() {
    // Derived colors computed from base colors
    this.primaryTextColor = invert(this.primaryColor);
    this.primaryBorderColor = mkBorder(this.primaryColor, this.darkMode);
    this.nodeBkg = this.primaryColor;
    // ... 300+ derivations
  }
}
```

**Implementation needed:**
1. Define base color properties that users set
2. Implement `calculate()` or `update_colors()` method
3. Derive secondary colors automatically:
   - Text colors (invert of background for contrast)
   - Border colors (darkened/lightened fill)
   - Per-diagram colors from base palette
4. Allow overrides after derivation

**Benefits:**
- Users only need to set 3-5 base colors
- Consistent, computed color relationships
- Automatic contrast handling

**Depends on:** Color manipulation utilities (mermaid-rs-fxb)

**Reference:** ~/projects/mermaid/packages/mermaid/src/themes/theme-default.js updateColors()
